The paper discusses a real-time application for robot grasping, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of vision data and machine learning, which are subfields of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), respectively. The paper proposes a policy for grasping based on haptic information, which involves decision-making and optimization, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
